The paper discusses the development of a compact deep neural network architecture for gesture classification using surface electromyography signals. This involves the use of machine learning classifiers, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on human-machine interfacing and device control, which falls under the category of "Human-Computer Interaction" (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques for feature extraction, which falls under the category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed architecture in embedded systems, which falls under the category of "Robotics" (cs.RO).
